data.name: backRules.Text
data.value:
Mastermind is a code-breaking game invented in 1970 by a postmaster and telecommunication expert named “Mordecai Meirowitz”.
This is a game for 2 players: codeBreaker(player1) and codeMaster(player2 or COM). The “codeMaster” will choose a pattern of four key Pegs. Duplicates are allowed which means that four pegs with the same colour are allowed. To swap colours just click on the pegs(right or left). Gray pegs are not considered. The secret code chosen is stored and hidden, visible at the end of the game only. The codebreaker needs to guess the pattern of numbers and their positions within 10, 8 or 6 turns. Codebreaker must remember his/her previous choice because after pressing the confirm button previous colours will be hidden. Each time the codebreaker will try to guess the pattern, the codeMaster will provides feedback placing from zero to four “key pegs” A white key peg for a correct colour peg in a wrong position, and a red peg for a correct colour in correct position.
The game will terminate when the codebreaker will guess the entire pattern or the attempts (depending the level chosen: easy 10, medium 8, hard 6) will run out. At the end of the game, restart button and playing time will be displayed.
